ENTRY            F0711   20251224   20260311   20260311       F107
SUBENT        F0711001   20251224   20260311   20260311       F107
BIB                 15         31
TITLE      Spectroscopic factors derived from 16O(d,n)17F
           measurements
AUTHOR     (C.J.Oliver,P.D.Forsyth,J.L.Hutton,G.Kaye,J.R.Mines)
INSTITUTE  (2UK LVP)
REFERENCE  (J,NP/A,127,567,1969)
FACILITY   (VDGT,2UK LVP)
INC-SOURCE Deuteron beam entered through a 7.5 um thick
           tantalum window. At 7 MeV the energy loss was 420 keV
           with a straggle of about 40 keV and at 11 and 12 MeV
           the energy loss was 300 keV. The beam was stop in a
           0.025 cm tantalum lining to the cell.
SAMPLE     Gaseous target of spectroscopically pure natural oxygen
           was used. The target chamber consisted of a piece of
           2.5 cm diameter 25 um thick stainless steel tube.
DETECTOR   (SPEC) Neutron time-of-flight spectrometer.
METHOD     (TOF) Neutron flight path of 3.46 m was used for the
           7.73 and 11 MeV measurements and a 6 m flight path was
           used for the 12 MeV measurements.
           Measurements were taken at a gas pressure of 60 cm Hg.
ANALYSIS   Neutron spectra were analyzed using a peak fitting
           program, based on that of Tepel (see REL-REF).
REL-REF    (M,,J.W.Tepel,J,NIM,40,100,1966)
MONITOR    (1-H-2(D,N)2-HE-3,,DA) Relative detector efficiency as
           a function of neutron energy and the absolute cross
           sections were obtained.
MONIT-REF  (,J.B.Marion+,B,FAST N.PH.,,80,1960)
ERR-ANALYS Energy resolution was about 3.5% for neutrons 5-8 MeV
           and about 2% for 10 MeV neutrons.
           (ERR-1) Uncertainty in normalization
HISTORY    (20050406C)
           (20251224U) SD: Small corrections in all Subents.
ENDBIB              31
COMMON               1          3
ERR-1
PER-CENT
         5.
ENDCOMMON            3
ENDSUBENT           38
SUBENT        F0711002   20251224   20260311   20260311       F107
BIB                  3          3
REACTION   (8-O-16(D,N)9-F-17,PAR,DA)
STATUS     (TABLE,,C.J.Oliver+,J,NP/A,127,567,1969) Table 1
HISTORY    (20251224U) SD: STATUS updated.
ENDBIB               3
